1
00:02:59,012 --> 00:02:59,712
Off-pump.

2
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:03,516
The superior vena cava is bypassed

3
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:05,485
so blood returns to the right atrium.

4
00:03:05,785 --> 00:03:07,153
That way, we don't need cardiopulmonary bypass

5
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:10,356
and the child suffers less trauma.

6
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:13,626
Prepare to clamp the superior vena cava.

7
00:03:13,793 --> 00:03:14,194
Understood.

8
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:28,241
Heart rate and blood pressure are stable.

9
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:44,090
Director Sheng's technique

10
00:03:44,123 --> 00:03:45,425
is truly eye-opening.

11
00:04:00,273 --> 00:04:00,807
Side-biting clamp.

12
00:04:03,009 --> 00:04:03,743
I'm preparing the right pulmonary artery.

13
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:04,444
Applying the clamp now.

14
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:05,144
Okay.

15
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:19,592
Heart rate 120.

16
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:20,526
Blood pressure 80.

17
00:04:20,893 --> 00:04:22,328
Oxygen saturation is holding

18
00:04:22,362 --> 00:04:23,196
at around 70.

19
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,808
While we're performing the anastomosis

20
00:04:35,808 --> 00:04:37,076
between the superior vena cava and pulmonary artery,

21
00:04:37,276 --> 00:04:39,278
we have to partially clamp the right pulmonary artery.

22
00:04:39,512 --> 00:04:40,513
But before that,

23
00:04:40,546 --> 00:04:42,215
the ductus arteriosus was already occluded.

24
00:04:43,149 --> 00:04:44,951
That would lower the oxygen level even further.

25
00:04:45,251 --> 00:04:46,519
Wouldn't the child become hypoxic?

26
00:04:47,553 --> 00:04:48,154
Normally,

27
00:04:48,154 --> 00:04:49,422
during the anastomosis,

28
00:04:49,689 --> 00:04:50,490
we keep

29
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:51,557
the ductus arteriosus open.

30
00:04:52,091 --> 00:04:53,226
That's safer.

31
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,961
But if we don't occlude it,

32
00:04:55,561 --> 00:04:57,630
the pulmonary artery pressure assessment will be inaccurate,

33
00:04:57,930 --> 00:04:58,431
and we won't be able to determine

34
00:04:58,431 --> 00:05:00,266
whether the Glenn procedure is indicated.

35
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,035
But once it's occluded,

36
00:05:02,235 --> 00:05:03,503
without cardiopulmonary bypass,

37
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:05,071
the child's oxygen saturation will fall.

38
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:07,206
So time is extremely tight.

39
00:05:07,874 --> 00:05:09,175
That's why an off-pump

40
00:05:09,175 --> 00:05:10,009
superior cavopulmonary anastomosis

41
00:05:10,009 --> 00:05:12,011
requires both courage and skill from the lead surgeon.

42
00:05:13,212 --> 00:05:14,914
Now it depends on Sheng Nian's hands.

43
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:25,758
The oxygen level is dropping fast.

44
00:05:25,792 --> 00:05:26,192
Director.

45
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:27,527
Xiao Lin.

46
00:05:28,528 --> 00:05:29,295
How long has it been

47
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:30,129
since you stood as first assistant?

48
00:05:33,032 --> 00:05:34,400
A long time. I don't remember.

49
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:04,731
Get ready to release the clamp.

50
00:06:04,797 --> 00:06:05,264
Okay.

51
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,007
The saturation is rising.

52
00:06:15,274 --> 00:06:16,042
Around 85.

53
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:23,983
Xiaohu, come take a look.

54
00:06:35,495 --> 00:06:36,195
Beautiful.

55
00:06:36,796 --> 00:06:37,964
Director Sheng really is

56
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:38,998
bold because of his skill.

57
00:06:40,466 --> 00:06:41,634
That was flawless.

58
00:06:43,002 --> 00:06:44,570
The one doing the occlusion earlier

59
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:46,506
and now assisting

60
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:47,774
is Director Lin Yi, right?

61
00:06:48,007 --> 00:06:48,441
Yes.

62
00:06:49,642 --> 00:06:50,410
No wonder.

63
00:06:50,843 --> 00:06:52,345
Those two work together perfectly.

64
00:06:53,446 --> 00:06:54,213
Lin Yi

65
00:06:54,447 --> 00:06:55,114
is also one of

66
00:06:55,148 --> 00:06:56,182
our very best surgeons.

67
00:06:56,549 --> 00:06:57,984
His open surgery goes without saying.

68
00:06:58,718 --> 00:06:59,552
And now,

69
00:06:59,652 --> 00:07:00,887
PDA occlusion,

70
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:01,988
TAVR,

71
00:07:02,522 --> 00:07:04,190
and all kinds of minimally invasive procedures—

72
00:07:04,357 --> 00:07:05,558
he does them all.

73
00:07:06,292 --> 00:07:07,493
Two top experts

74
00:07:07,527 --> 00:07:08,561
working in perfect coordination.

75
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:10,763
That's the perfect example of

76
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:12,331
one plus one being greater than two.

77
00:07:13,065 --> 00:07:14,200
Everyone doing what they do best,

78
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:15,401
and every skill put to full use.

79
00:07:15,835 --> 00:07:17,069
Everything is for the patient.

80
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,304
Especially children.

81
00:07:18,805 --> 00:07:20,640
We should achieve the best result

82
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:23,009
with the least trauma.

83
00:07:23,509 --> 00:07:24,076
Now,

84
00:07:24,143 --> 00:07:26,646
Sheng Nian has pushed minimally invasive cardiac surgery

85
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,648
to a whole new level.

86
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:31,784
A three-centimeter incision.

87
00:07:32,752 --> 00:07:34,487
Sixty minutes from skin incision to closure.

88
00:07:36,155 --> 00:07:37,323
That was a beautiful operation.

89
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:39,559
When the oxygen level dropped,

90
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:40,893
I was really nervous.

91
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:50,036
This is one of the children

92
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:51,070
I operated on in Xinjiang

93
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:52,572
years ago.

94
00:07:53,606 --> 00:07:54,307
At the time,

95
00:07:54,607 --> 00:07:55,608
she had complex tetralogy of Fallot.

96
00:07:56,042 --> 00:07:57,210
Everyone thought she wouldn't survive.

97
00:07:57,543 --> 00:07:59,345
But the surgery was a success.

98
00:08:00,112 --> 00:08:02,148
Now she's been admitted to a top university.

99
00:08:02,615 --> 00:08:03,616
She came to share the good news.

100
00:08:05,284 --> 00:08:06,319
At moments like this,

101
00:08:06,752 --> 00:08:08,054
I feel that as a doctor,

102
00:08:09,121 --> 00:08:10,423
this is the greatest sense of achievement.

103
00:08:14,227 --> 00:08:15,561
Take today's child.

104
00:08:16,195 --> 00:08:17,797
A small-incision, off-pump procedure

105
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:19,932
means the lead surgeon

106
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,234
has to take a major risk.

107
00:08:22,068 --> 00:08:23,369
But to spare the child

108
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:24,971
so much suffering

109
00:08:25,371 --> 00:08:26,372
and help them recover sooner,

110
00:08:27,573 --> 00:08:28,674
do you think

111
00:08:29,275 --> 00:08:29,876
that risk is worth taking?

112
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:31,744
Yes.

113
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:34,213
Only after seeing

114
00:08:34,213 --> 00:08:35,448
such an elegant operation firsthand

115
00:08:36,215 --> 00:08:37,250
do I understand

116
00:08:37,450 --> 00:08:38,451
why you dared choose

117
00:08:38,451 --> 00:08:39,585
such a complex approach.

118
00:08:39,952 --> 00:08:41,454
So I believe

119
00:08:42,922 --> 00:08:44,023
that in clinical care,

120
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:46,292
there is only one best method:

121
00:08:46,826 --> 00:08:48,094
the one that maximizes

122
00:08:48,094 --> 00:08:49,228
the patient's interests.

123
00:08:49,829 --> 00:08:50,630
You may

124
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,231
have to shoulder pressure

125
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:53,799
and face doubt.

126
00:08:55,368 --> 00:08:56,769
You should understand that.

127
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,308
But that is exactly the mission

128
00:09:02,308 --> 00:09:04,010
of an excellent cardiac surgeon.

129
00:09:04,677 --> 00:09:05,878
Always focus on

130
00:09:06,078 --> 00:09:07,446
challenge and innovation.

131
00:09:10,316 --> 00:09:11,183
Keep improving your skills.

132
00:09:12,351 --> 00:09:14,320
Challenge boldly, practice carefully.

133
00:09:17,089 --> 00:09:17,623
Lin Yi,

134
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:20,226
you are the ideal person

135
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:20,993
to carry that mission.

136
00:09:21,761 --> 00:09:22,929
But not you alone.

137
00:09:24,764 --> 00:09:25,665
I will work to raise

138
00:09:25,765 --> 00:09:27,800
our department's academic standing

139
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,001
and influence.

140
00:09:29,468 --> 00:09:30,169
Only then

141
00:09:30,836 --> 00:09:31,804
can I clear away

142
00:09:31,804 --> 00:09:33,439
all obstacles in your path

143
00:09:35,308 --> 00:09:36,509
and help the best people

144
00:09:36,676 --> 00:09:38,010
see the future sooner.

145
00:09:38,811 --> 00:09:39,478
That is my mission

146
00:09:39,512 --> 00:09:40,680
as department director.

147
00:09:46,953 --> 00:09:48,187
Why are you so good to me?

148
00:09:51,324 --> 00:09:52,591
It's not only for you.

149
00:09:53,993 --> 00:09:56,429
If your skills reach a higher level,

150
00:09:57,363 --> 00:09:58,331
our department's

151
00:09:58,364 --> 00:09:59,265
strength and status

152
00:09:59,398 --> 00:10:00,566
will rise with them.

153
00:10:01,233 --> 00:10:01,767
It's a win-win.

154
00:10:02,735 --> 00:10:03,736
In the end,

155
00:10:04,203 --> 00:10:04,870
the patients benefit.

156
00:10:07,073 --> 00:10:08,007
I'm sorry, Director.

157
00:10:08,641 --> 00:10:10,376
About the artificial heart last time,

158
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:12,244
and that case

159
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,245
with the one-centimeter ASD,

160
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:15,147
I doubted you.

161
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:19,885
The one-centimeter ASD?

162
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:22,555
Yes. When I first saw it,

163
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:24,123
I thought choosing open surgery directly

164
00:10:24,323 --> 00:10:25,424
was far too aggressive.

165
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:27,526
Only now do I understand

166
00:10:28,394 --> 00:10:29,295
that you had already balanced

167
00:10:29,328 --> 00:10:30,162
the trauma

168
00:10:30,496 --> 00:10:31,430
against the benefit.

169
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,467
Of course.

170
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:36,635
But

171
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:38,871
how did you learn

172
00:10:39,105 --> 00:10:40,106
about that child?

173
00:10:40,673 --> 00:10:41,440
Who told you?

174
00:10:46,846 --> 00:10:47,413
It doesn't matter.

175
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:49,248
Lin Yi,

176
00:10:50,449 --> 00:10:51,951
I want us to agree on something.

177
00:10:53,352 --> 00:10:54,353
From now on, whenever

178
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,155
something involves the two of us,

179
00:10:56,756 --> 00:10:57,990
no matter what was said

180
00:10:58,691 --> 00:10:59,358
or done,

181
00:11:00,593 --> 00:11:01,894
if you don't hear it from me personally,

182
00:11:03,229 --> 00:11:04,030
don't believe it.

183
00:11:05,931 --> 00:11:07,400
And if I don't tell you myself,

184
00:11:08,034 --> 00:11:09,001
don't believe it either.

185
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:10,636
Can we do that?

186
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:14,974
Yes.

187
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:18,878
Let today be a beginning.

188
00:11:19,412 --> 00:11:20,746
From now on,

189
00:11:21,047 --> 00:11:22,081
we can operate together more often.

190
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:29,355
So what's the situation now?

191
00:11:29,655 --> 00:11:30,890
Have the two departments

192
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:32,758
completely stopped cooperating?

193
00:11:33,559 --> 00:11:34,894
Cardiac Surgery handled

194
00:11:34,927 --> 00:11:36,562
the entire hybrid procedure alone.

195
00:11:37,463 --> 00:11:38,230
That's exactly

196
00:11:38,230 --> 00:11:39,665
what Sheng Nian has been planning.

197
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:42,802
From the one-stop valve procedures

198
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,804
to today's hybrid operation,

199
00:11:45,638 --> 00:11:46,872
he wants to keep every service

200
00:11:46,972 --> 00:11:47,973
inside Cardiac Surgery

201
00:11:48,407 --> 00:11:49,842
and solve everything within his own department.

202
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:52,044
It's obvious

203
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:54,914
you've been worrying yourself sick over the department.

204
00:11:57,783 --> 00:11:58,551
Did you hear

205
00:11:58,551 --> 00:11:59,652
someone say something about me?

206
00:12:00,486 --> 00:12:01,721
No.

207
00:12:02,254 --> 00:12:04,590
Everyone knows our relationship.

208
00:12:04,824 --> 00:12:05,424
Even if they complain,

209
00:12:05,424 --> 00:12:06,892
they won't do it in front of me.

210
00:12:07,893 --> 00:12:08,561
But

211
00:12:08,761 --> 00:12:09,862
I have heard about

212
00:12:09,929 --> 00:12:11,730
some of Director Xiaofeng's drastic measures.

213
00:12:12,264 --> 00:12:13,132
I had no choice.

214
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,267
At a time like this,

215
00:12:15,968 --> 00:12:17,403
we can only rely on our skills, reputation,

216
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:19,205
and service to keep patients.

217
00:12:21,807 --> 00:12:23,209
I've pushed everyone so hard.

218
00:12:24,276 --> 00:12:25,077
If they resent me,

219
00:12:25,478 --> 00:12:26,045
I'll accept it.

220
00:12:29,115 --> 00:12:31,050
You also need to take care of yourself.

221
00:12:31,684 --> 00:12:33,586
Physical stamina has limits.

222
00:12:38,324 --> 00:12:38,824
What about you?

223
00:12:40,126 --> 00:12:41,727
Is your medical consortium work almost over?

224
00:12:41,894 --> 00:12:42,928
It's already finished.

225
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,965
Running between both sides was exhausting,

226
00:12:46,966 --> 00:12:48,434
but at least it produced results.

227
00:12:51,203 --> 00:12:52,471
At least one of us

228
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:54,006
has something to show for it.

229
00:12:55,174 --> 00:12:56,075
I can imagine

230
00:12:56,709 --> 00:12:58,410
how much pressure you're under.

231
00:12:59,745 --> 00:13:00,846
I haven't seen Ouyang

232
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,481
coming around for business lately.

233
00:13:03,382 --> 00:13:05,451
That's when I realized how much pressure your department is under.

234
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:07,186
It's not entirely because of work.

235
00:13:09,155 --> 00:13:09,755
The two of us

236
00:13:09,922 --> 00:13:11,323
agreed to keep our distance.

237
00:13:12,925 --> 00:13:13,626
Why?

238
00:13:15,895 --> 00:13:16,796
You and I

239
00:13:17,263 --> 00:13:18,464
really are in the same boat.

240
00:13:19,932 --> 00:13:20,833
On New Year's Eve,

241
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,268
I broke up with her too.

242
00:13:26,605 --> 00:13:27,239
But when did

243
00:13:27,239 --> 00:13:28,841
the two of you get together?

244
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:31,410
How did I know nothing about it?

245
00:13:32,711 --> 00:13:33,746
Strictly speaking,

246
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,848
it ended before it really began.

247
00:13:42,254 --> 00:13:43,289
We both realized

248
00:13:43,856 --> 00:13:45,090
our feelings for each other

249
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:47,760
were starting to affect our lives

250
00:13:47,793 --> 00:13:48,494
and our work.

251
00:13:50,229 --> 00:13:51,197
So, without even saying it,

252
00:13:52,364 --> 00:13:53,799
we both chose to take a step back.

253
00:13:57,036 --> 00:13:57,670
Anyway,

254
00:13:59,004 --> 00:13:59,905
we'll each live our own lives

255
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:01,440
and stop disturbing one another.

256
00:14:04,476 --> 00:14:05,711
But the two of you

257
00:14:05,711 --> 00:14:07,112
will inevitably cross paths

258
00:14:07,112 --> 00:14:08,547
at work in the future.

259
00:14:09,114 --> 00:14:09,882
What then?

260
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:13,686
All right. You don't have to answer.

261
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:15,487
I'm the same as you.

262
00:14:18,324 --> 00:14:18,757
Come on.

263
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,361
Two of a kind.

264
00:14:23,495 --> 00:14:23,796
Mom.

265
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:25,030
You really don't have to wait for me.

266
00:14:25,264 --> 00:14:25,865
Go to sleep first.

267
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:27,366
I'll come home when I'm done.

268
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,391
Hello, Dr. Xu.

269
00:14:52,925 --> 00:14:54,693
Director Sheng doesn't seem to be in his office.

270
00:14:54,827 --> 00:14:56,528
The lights are off too.

271
00:14:57,596 --> 00:14:58,931
I don't know where he is either.

272
00:14:59,531 --> 00:15:00,366
He only said

273
00:15:00,532 --> 00:15:01,734
to wait outside his office.

274
00:15:03,035 --> 00:15:04,003
Did an emergency surgery

275
00:15:04,003 --> 00:15:04,803
come up suddenly?

276
00:15:05,204 --> 00:15:06,405
Why don't you call and ask him?

277
00:15:07,373 --> 00:15:07,773
Okay.

278
00:15:08,474 --> 00:15:09,074
Thank you.

279
00:15:09,675 --> 00:15:10,809
I'll wait here.

280
00:15:11,644 --> 00:15:12,077
All right.

281
00:15:48,013 --> 00:15:48,647
Director Sheng.

282
00:15:48,947 --> 00:15:50,482
I'm outside your office.

283
00:16:00,392 --> 00:16:01,894
Wait a little. I'm busy.

284
00:16:03,996 --> 00:16:05,264
Okay. Take your time.

285
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:06,265
There's no rush.

286
00:16:55,614 --> 00:16:56,648
Director Sheng, you're back.

287
00:16:57,149 --> 00:16:57,850
What are you doing here

288
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:58,384
so early?

289
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:01,954
Didn't you tell me

290
00:17:01,954 --> 00:17:02,955
to wait here?

291
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:05,824
You didn't stay here

292
00:17:05,824 --> 00:17:06,992
all night, did you?

293
00:17:08,127 --> 00:17:08,594
I did.

294
00:17:09,895 --> 00:17:10,996
Did you need something from me?

295
00:17:11,663 --> 00:17:13,232
I originally wanted to ask

296
00:17:13,232 --> 00:17:14,533
about product use,

297
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,402
but the issue has been resolved.

298
00:17:18,771 --> 00:17:19,071
Director Sheng.

299
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:19,705
Director Zhou.

300
00:17:20,672 --> 00:17:22,374
Look how honest this girl is.

301
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,076
She sat here all night.

302
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:26,712
She doesn't know how to adapt at all.

303
00:17:28,347 --> 00:17:29,615
You told me to wait a moment.

304
00:17:29,681 --> 00:17:31,150
I thought you'd gone into surgery.

305
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:32,050
Yes.

306
00:17:32,751 --> 00:17:33,519
It was my fault.

307
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:35,521
I should have updated you.

308
00:17:36,388 --> 00:17:37,589
You should've called me too.

309
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:39,558
Remember next time.

310
00:17:39,925 --> 00:17:40,759
All right. Go home.

311
00:17:40,926 --> 00:17:41,393
Get some proper rest.

312
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:42,094
Okay.

313
00:18:08,987 --> 00:18:09,955
A one-centimeter ASD.

314
00:18:10,556 --> 00:18:11,757
How did you learn

315
00:18:11,990 --> 00:18:12,991
about that child?

316
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:14,326
Who told you?

317
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:16,095
Director Sheng,

318
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:18,063
about our Qianqian's

319
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:19,531
atrial septal defect—

320
00:18:19,998 --> 00:18:20,766
we've already consulted

321
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:21,934
many hospitals.

322
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:23,268
Manager Ouyang

323
00:18:23,335 --> 00:18:24,236
told us many times

324
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:25,571
that you're

325
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:26,371
a leading expert at Dongli Hospital.

326
00:18:26,638 --> 00:18:27,406
Please

327
00:18:27,406 --> 00:18:28,407
help us find a solution.

328
00:18:30,709 --> 00:18:32,478
Aren't you usually pretty quick-witted?

329
00:18:32,811 --> 00:18:34,313
When he stopped replying after midnight,

330
00:18:34,546 --> 00:18:36,014
you should've realized and left.

331
00:18:37,416 --> 00:18:38,951
Ever since the artificial heart surgery,

332
00:18:39,051 --> 00:18:40,486
he's been holding a grudge against me.

333
00:18:40,719 --> 00:18:42,588
Last time at the restaurant, he only vented half of it.

334
00:18:43,355 --> 00:18:44,289
If I don't let him

335
00:18:44,323 --> 00:18:45,357
get the rest out,

336
00:18:45,624 --> 00:18:47,226
I can leave this time, but what about next time?

337
00:18:47,526 --> 00:18:48,627
Or the time after that?

338
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:49,695
Fine.

339
00:18:49,995 --> 00:18:50,996
That big shot really

340
00:18:51,029 --> 00:18:52,431
isn't very broad-minded.

341
00:18:53,065 --> 00:18:54,366
But we can't afford to offend him.

342
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:56,201
So let's put up with it for the money.

343
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:57,870
After all, over the past few months,

344
00:18:58,070 --> 00:18:58,971
his order volume

345
00:18:59,004 --> 00:18:59,705
has still been considerable.

346
00:19:00,205 --> 00:19:01,673
I was just about to mention that.

347
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,041
Don't you think

348
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:04,810
the recent orders from Dongli Cardiac Surgery

349
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:05,677
are strange?

350
00:19:05,944 --> 00:19:06,945
They suddenly ordered so much.

351
00:19:07,546 --> 00:19:08,447
Their business

352
00:19:08,514 --> 00:19:09,715
has grown far too fast.

353
00:19:10,115 --> 00:19:11,049
I have a batch

354
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:12,518
of bioprosthetic valves.

355
00:19:13,385 --> 00:19:14,486
They're still within their shelf life,

356
00:19:15,254 --> 00:19:16,321
but they're expiring soon.

357
00:19:17,189 --> 00:19:18,824
I'd like the director to help use some of them.

358
00:19:19,591 --> 00:19:20,092
What?

359
00:19:20,959 --> 00:19:22,594
You think business is too good?

360
00:19:22,961 --> 00:19:23,762
Listen.

361
00:19:23,929 --> 00:19:26,131
We only handle shipping and payment.

362
00:19:26,365 --> 00:19:27,633
Everything else is none of our concern.

363
00:19:27,966 --> 00:19:28,467
Also,

364
00:19:28,867 --> 00:19:29,735
the director of the Heart Center

365
00:19:29,801 --> 00:19:30,936
will be decided soon.

366
00:19:31,603 --> 00:19:33,071
It'll definitely be Sheng Nian.

367
00:19:33,438 --> 00:19:34,373
You're that certain?

368
00:19:34,706 --> 00:19:35,274
Why?

369
00:19:35,641 --> 00:19:37,409
Because Sheng Nian has more seniority.

370
00:19:37,409 --> 00:19:38,410
And that's not all.

371
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:40,412
He has Lin Yi on his side.

372
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,414
He's won Lin Yi over

373
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:43,348
completely.

374
00:19:43,782 --> 00:19:44,983
At this critical moment,

375
00:19:45,117 --> 00:19:46,685
Lin Yi and Fang Xiaoran

376
00:19:46,718 --> 00:19:47,553
have also broken up.

377
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,788
That last personal tie is gone.

378
00:19:50,322 --> 00:19:50,956
Zhou Xiaofeng

379
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:52,424
has completely lost Lin Yi.

380
00:19:52,891 --> 00:19:54,593
The tide has turned against him.

381
00:19:56,228 --> 00:19:57,329
All right, I'm driving.

382
00:19:57,396 --> 00:19:58,163
I can't talk anymore.

383
00:19:58,263 --> 00:19:58,797
Hang up.

384
00:19:59,731 --> 00:20:00,365
Okay, boss.

385
00:20:06,905 --> 00:20:07,606
Yete.

386
00:20:08,006 --> 00:20:08,807
Move Qiangwei in Bed One

387
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:09,975
to a three-person room today.

388
00:20:10,175 --> 00:20:11,009
Help her pack.

389
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:11,743
No problem.

390
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:12,144
Okay.

391
00:20:12,511 --> 00:20:13,545
Hadn't she already settled in?

392
00:20:13,612 --> 00:20:14,646
Why is she moving?

393
00:20:15,447 --> 00:20:17,416
It seems the patient requested it.

394
00:20:17,516 --> 00:20:18,917
Probably financial pressure.

395
00:20:19,318 --> 00:20:20,385
Director Zhou approved it personally.

396
00:20:20,786 --> 00:20:21,887
Director Zhou approved it?

397
00:20:24,389 --> 00:20:26,291
Is there something special about this patient?

398
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:28,327
Why would Director Zhou handle such a small matter?

399
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:30,729
Qiangwei was an old patient

400
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:32,130
of the Heart Center two years ago.

401
00:20:32,664 --> 00:20:33,932
Her life story is quite tragic.

402
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:36,168
She was abandoned as a child

403
00:20:36,168 --> 00:20:36,969
because of heart disease

404
00:20:37,002 --> 00:20:37,970
and grew up in an orphanage.

405
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:39,438
Later, after much hardship,

406
00:20:39,471 --> 00:20:40,472
she met someone she loved.

407
00:20:40,839 --> 00:20:41,773
They had a wonderful relationship.

408
00:20:42,474 --> 00:20:43,642
But shortly before the wedding,

409
00:20:43,675 --> 00:20:44,643
they were in a car accident.

410
00:20:45,277 --> 00:20:46,712
Her fiancé protected her

411
00:20:46,712 --> 00:20:47,613
and was badly injured.

412
00:20:48,814 --> 00:20:50,015
He didn't survive.

413
00:20:51,516 --> 00:20:52,718
What a cruel twist of fate.

414
00:20:53,652 --> 00:20:54,987
You found it? Let's go.

415
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:55,387
Okay.

416
00:20:59,424 --> 00:21:02,027
Actually, patients like her, Aunt Yang,

417
00:21:02,828 --> 00:21:04,563
Hua'er, and several others—

418
00:21:05,230 --> 00:21:06,231
their surgeries back then

419
00:21:06,231 --> 00:21:07,332
were all performed by my brother and Lin Yi

420
00:21:07,366 --> 00:21:08,200
working together.

421
00:21:09,668 --> 00:21:10,569
At that time,

422
00:21:10,602 --> 00:21:12,304
Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery were united.

423
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:14,239
The whole Heart Center felt hopeful.

424
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:15,974
Everyone was full of energy.

425
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:17,876
So

426
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:19,711
seeing Qiangwei now

427
00:21:19,878 --> 00:21:20,946
brings back a lot of emotions.

428
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,748
I heard about that too.

429
00:21:23,315 --> 00:21:24,583
When President Cui was here,

430
00:21:24,883 --> 00:21:26,084
the Heart Center model

431
00:21:26,451 --> 00:21:27,886
was always developing positively.

432
00:21:39,431 --> 00:21:40,198
What's the patient's condition?

433
00:21:40,599 --> 00:21:41,566
Female, 24 years old.

434
00:21:41,733 --> 00:21:42,601
A foreign object penetrated the chest.

435
00:21:42,601 --> 00:21:43,602
Cardiac injury is suspected.

436
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:44,569
During transport, Yiyi's

437
00:21:44,569 --> 00:21:45,437
heart rate and blood pressure were relatively stable.

438
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:46,471
Send her to the resuscitation room first.

439
00:21:47,606 --> 00:21:49,007
Can you hear your mother?

440
00:21:49,574 --> 00:21:51,076
Can you hear your mother?

441
00:21:51,843 --> 00:21:52,344
Yiyi.

442
00:21:52,944 --> 00:21:53,645
Yiyi.

443
00:21:54,212 --> 00:21:54,813
Yiyi.

444
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:55,681
Family members, wait outside.

445
00:22:02,721 --> 00:22:03,288
What happened?

446
00:22:03,388 --> 00:22:04,289
How did she get hurt so badly?

447
00:22:04,456 --> 00:22:05,357
Her brother is a carpenter.

448
00:22:05,390 --> 00:22:05,924
He was working,

449
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:06,725
and his sister came up behind him

450
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:07,726
to surprise him.

451
00:22:07,893 --> 00:22:08,927
The nail gun accidentally fired,

452
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:10,295
and a nail went straight into her heart.

453
00:22:10,395 --> 00:22:11,163
Are we sure it was an accident?

454
00:22:11,263 --> 00:22:11,863
It must have been.

455
00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:12,764
They're siblings, after all.

456
00:22:12,798 --> 00:22:13,832
Their parents are frantic outside.

457
00:22:18,103 --> 00:22:18,704
Are we ready?

458
00:22:19,237 --> 00:22:19,638
Director.

459
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:24,810
Are the pre-transfusion test results

460
00:22:24,810 --> 00:22:25,410
back yet?

461
00:22:25,644 --> 00:22:26,111
Not yet.

462
00:22:27,312 --> 00:22:28,046
Everyone use full protection.

463
00:22:28,246 --> 00:22:28,613
Okay.

464
00:22:36,855 --> 00:22:37,723
The patient's venous pressure is rising,

465
00:22:37,723 --> 00:22:38,423
arterial pressure is falling,

466
00:22:38,423 --> 00:22:39,124
and her heart rate is very fast.

467
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:39,758
What's the cause?

468
00:22:40,092 --> 00:22:41,326
Strongly suspect cardiac tamponade.

469
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:42,561
Then what?

470
00:22:42,994 --> 00:22:44,396
We need to move quickly.

471
00:22:44,429 --> 00:22:45,163
Every second counts.

472
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:45,764
Get to the point.

473
00:22:46,465 --> 00:22:47,399
Open the pericardium first

474
00:22:47,666 --> 00:22:48,767
to relieve the tamponade.

475
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,736
Then place a purse-string suture around the rupture

476
00:22:50,869 --> 00:22:51,636
and remove the nail.

477
00:22:53,805 --> 00:22:54,406
Hold ventilation.

478
00:22:54,573 --> 00:22:55,040
Hold ventilation.

479
00:23:13,959 --> 00:23:14,760
It's so distended.

480
00:23:15,994 --> 00:23:16,762
If she'd arrived any later,

481
00:23:16,762 --> 00:23:17,529
she would've died.

482
00:23:23,201 --> 00:23:23,835
Prepare to open the pericardium.

483
00:23:24,102 --> 00:23:24,403
Okay.

484
00:23:31,343 --> 00:23:32,010
Increase suction.

485
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:32,677
Increase suction.

486
00:23:41,987 --> 00:23:42,721
Blood pressure is rising.

487
00:23:43,155 --> 00:23:43,989
Cardiac tamponade relieved.

488
00:23:47,225 --> 00:23:47,692
There it is.

489
00:23:48,126 --> 00:23:48,527
Director.

490
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:49,828
Should we prepare cardiopulmonary bypass?

491
00:23:50,962 --> 00:23:51,263
No.

492
00:23:52,564 --> 00:23:53,031
We'll operate on the beating heart.

493
00:24:21,893 --> 00:24:22,194
Hello.

494
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,295
Excuse me, how do I get to

495
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:24,629
the sixth floor?

496
00:24:25,263 --> 00:24:26,131
The elevator is over there.

497
00:24:26,832 --> 00:24:27,332
I don't want the elevator.

498
00:24:27,365 --> 00:24:28,533
Where are the stairs?

499
00:24:28,934 --> 00:24:29,634
I don't know. I don't know.

500
00:24:30,569 --> 00:24:31,403
The lab results are back.

501
00:24:31,403 --> 00:24:31,903
Hello.

502
00:24:32,170 --> 00:24:32,771
Excuse me,

503
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:34,506
where are the stairs?

504
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:42,347
Where are you going?

505
00:24:42,881 --> 00:24:43,448
The operating room.

506
00:24:43,915 --> 00:24:45,050
This is the emergency building.

507
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:46,518
Take the elevator to the third floor,

508
00:24:46,518 --> 00:24:47,519
then transfer to the outpatient building.

509
00:24:58,630 --> 00:24:59,431
Not that way.

510
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:01,366
I'll take you.

511
00:25:11,643 --> 00:25:12,277
Tighten the purse-string.

512
00:25:16,281 --> 00:25:17,015
Prepare to remove the nail.

513
00:25:34,766 --> 00:25:35,734
No active bleeding.

514
00:25:41,573 --> 00:25:41,907
Needle.

515
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:53,351
Are you sleepy at the operating table?

516
00:25:53,985 --> 00:25:54,686
Since the surgery began,

517
00:25:54,719 --> 00:25:55,921
you've yawned three times.

518
00:25:56,521 --> 00:25:58,123
No. I can keep going.

519
00:25:58,523 --> 00:25:59,357
Chenchen, have someone replace her.

520
00:25:59,691 --> 00:26:00,825
Director, I can continue.

521
00:26:01,159 --> 00:26:02,027
The patient can't afford for you to.

522
00:26:03,128 --> 00:26:03,528
Step down.

523
00:26:12,904 --> 00:26:14,205
Xiao Zhu, are you in the office?

524
00:26:14,306 --> 00:26:15,473
Come to OR Three.

525
00:26:15,874 --> 00:26:16,675
Remember to scrub in.

526
00:26:19,277 --> 00:26:19,878
Dr. Ye.

527
00:26:20,045 --> 00:26:21,212
Dr. Ye, what's wrong?

528
00:26:21,546 --> 00:26:22,280
Dr. Qiao.

529
00:26:23,014 --> 00:26:23,415
I'll take over.

530
00:26:23,715 --> 00:26:24,482
What's wrong, Sisi?

531
00:26:24,649 --> 00:26:25,183
Lay her flat first.

532
00:26:26,985 --> 00:26:27,652
Chenchen, call for help.

533
00:26:29,921 --> 00:26:30,889
Hello, OR Three.

534
00:26:30,922 --> 00:26:31,756
Dr. Ye has fainted.

535
00:26:31,823 --> 00:26:32,490
We need assistance.

536
00:26:32,791 --> 00:26:34,326
Rapid breathing and tachycardia.

537
00:26:34,626 --> 00:26:35,126
Everyone stay calm.

538
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:36,561
Keep her airway open.

539
00:26:41,766 --> 00:26:42,834
The operating room is right over there.

540
00:26:43,735 --> 00:26:45,036
In a case like your daughter's,

541
00:26:45,203 --> 00:26:46,204
with that much blood loss,

542
00:26:46,471 --> 00:26:47,072
she'll definitely need

543
00:26:47,172 --> 00:26:48,273
a transfusion during surgery.

544
00:26:49,307 --> 00:26:50,241
I don't know whether

545
00:26:50,709 --> 00:26:51,343
the hospital has

546
00:26:51,409 --> 00:26:52,310
enough blood prepared.

547
00:26:52,711 --> 00:26:53,545
Then what should we do?

548
00:26:54,012 --> 00:26:55,280
I can donate. I'll donate.

549
00:26:55,614 --> 00:26:56,214
Where do I go?

550
00:26:57,449 --> 00:26:58,249
Who told you to come?

551
00:26:58,383 --> 00:26:59,117
What are you doing here?

552
00:26:59,117 --> 00:26:59,884
Your mother and I will handle it.

553
00:26:59,884 --> 00:27:00,752
Just tell me where I can donate.

554
00:27:00,919 --> 00:27:02,287
Please tell me.

555
00:27:02,354 --> 00:27:03,722
I want to give my blood back to my sister.

556
00:27:03,855 --> 00:27:04,155
Don't.

557
00:27:04,155 --> 00:27:05,023
Please tell me. Calm down.

558
00:27:05,123 --> 00:27:05,824
Calm down.

559
00:27:05,991 --> 00:27:07,592
Please save my sister.

560
00:27:07,625 --> 00:27:08,893
That's the brother, right?

561
00:27:09,094 --> 00:27:10,095
Yes. Just imagine—

562
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:10,962
how could he fire a nail

563
00:27:10,996 --> 00:27:11,963
into his sister's heart?

564
00:27:11,997 --> 00:27:13,732
Please, tell me.

565
00:27:13,765 --> 00:27:14,466
Stop shouting.

566
00:27:14,566 --> 00:27:15,567
Family of Yan Yiyi.

567
00:27:16,768 --> 00:27:17,502
Doctor, we're here.

568
00:27:17,936 --> 00:27:18,803
We're here.

569
00:27:18,837 --> 00:27:19,604
How is Yiyi?

570
00:27:20,071 --> 00:27:21,272
The nail has been removed.

571
00:27:21,906 --> 00:27:23,608
The rupture has also been repaired.

572
00:27:24,175 --> 00:27:24,943
The surgery was successful.

573
00:27:25,844 --> 00:27:26,311
Good.

574
00:27:27,712 --> 00:27:28,313
But

575
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:29,914
her condition is still serious.

576
00:27:30,882 --> 00:27:31,716
She needs to stay for observation.

577
00:27:32,183 --> 00:27:33,318
She'll go to the ICU first.

578
00:27:34,319 --> 00:27:34,953
Then...

579
00:27:35,253 --> 00:27:36,855
when can we see her?

580
00:27:37,322 --> 00:27:38,156
If anything else comes up,

581
00:27:38,189 --> 00:27:39,190
another doctor will contact you.

582
00:27:40,225 --> 00:27:40,759
Later, you can go

583
00:27:40,759 --> 00:27:41,192
to the general ICU

584
00:27:41,192 --> 00:27:41,559
to see her.

585
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:42,127
Okay, okay.

586
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,128
Thank you. Thank you.

587
00:27:43,395 --> 00:27:44,162
Thank you, doctor.

588
00:27:45,630 --> 00:27:46,064
She's okay now.

589
00:27:46,965 --> 00:27:47,799
Yiyi is okay.

590
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:48,800
Mom.

591
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:50,368
Why did you come?

592
00:27:51,069 --> 00:27:52,003
I don't want you here.

593
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:53,672
Stay home.

594
00:27:54,706 --> 00:27:55,407
All right, all right.

595
00:27:55,874 --> 00:27:57,175
Your sister is okay.

596
00:27:57,909 --> 00:28:01,513
She's okay. She's okay.

597
00:28:03,281 --> 00:28:05,383
She's okay now.

598
00:28:08,653 --> 00:28:10,188
Yan Yiyi, female, age 24.

599
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:10,955
Four hours ago,

600
00:28:10,955 --> 00:28:11,990
a nail gun fired into her heart,

601
00:28:11,990 --> 00:28:13,425
causing cardiac rupture and tamponade.

602
00:28:13,491 --> 00:28:14,759
She underwent removal of the cardiac foreign body.

603
00:28:15,293 --> 00:28:16,327
Did she experience hypotension?

604
00:28:16,728 --> 00:28:17,729
She was hypotensive on arrival.

605
00:28:17,896 --> 00:28:18,797
After epinephrine,

606
00:28:18,797 --> 00:28:19,197
she stabilized.

607
00:28:19,397 --> 00:28:20,532
Were her pupils checked?

608
00:28:20,732 --> 00:28:21,366
Pupil size

609
00:28:21,433 --> 00:28:22,600
and light reflex were both normal.

610
00:28:35,113 --> 00:28:35,647
Sisi.

611
00:28:36,014 --> 00:28:36,948
Here, drink some water.

612
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:38,516
Slowly.

613
00:28:40,051 --> 00:28:40,452
How are you?

614
00:28:40,919 --> 00:28:41,319
Director Zhou.

615
00:28:41,319 --> 00:28:41,586
Director.

616
00:28:42,353 --> 00:28:43,121
Nothing serious.

617
00:28:43,354 --> 00:28:44,756
It was probably due to exhaustion

618
00:28:44,789 --> 00:28:45,757
and hypoglycemia.

619
00:28:48,126 --> 00:28:48,693
Are you okay?

620
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:49,994
I've recovered.

621
00:28:50,195 --> 00:28:51,196
I feel fine now.

622
00:28:52,430 --> 00:28:53,198
Has anything similar

623
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:54,199
happened before?

624
00:28:56,134 --> 00:28:56,568
No.

625
00:28:59,504 --> 00:29:00,905
Tell me if you can't handle it.

626
00:29:02,006 --> 00:29:03,708
I know. I'm fine.

627
00:29:04,509 --> 00:29:05,110
When you go home,

628
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:05,844
get a good night's sleep.

629
00:29:06,311 --> 00:29:07,112
And don't work this weekend.

630
00:29:07,212 --> 00:29:07,879
Stay home and rest.

631
00:29:08,613 --> 00:29:09,447
No, no, no.

632
00:29:09,714 --> 00:29:11,483
There's still so much work this weekend.

633
00:29:11,950 --> 00:29:13,685
And everyone has been busy lately.

634
00:29:14,719 --> 00:29:15,153
Director,

635
00:29:15,653 --> 00:29:17,122
you have even more pressure and fatigue.

636
00:29:17,589 --> 00:29:18,690
I'm your assistant.

637
00:29:18,957 --> 00:29:20,291
I should do as much as I can.

638
00:29:20,525 --> 00:29:21,426
I've already arranged it.

639
00:29:22,026 --> 00:29:22,894
You will rest at home.

640
00:29:23,194 --> 00:29:23,728
That's final.

641
00:29:24,395 --> 00:29:24,629
I...

642
00:29:24,896 --> 00:29:25,630
Listen to the director.

643
00:29:28,133 --> 00:29:29,167
I'm really fine.

644
00:29:43,715 --> 00:29:44,315
Do you know she hasn't slept

645
00:29:44,315 --> 00:29:45,517
for 24 hours?

646
00:29:47,385 --> 00:29:48,286
Do you have to push people this hard

647
00:29:48,353 --> 00:29:49,554
just for a promotion?

648
00:29:55,994 --> 00:29:56,628
Didn't every young doctor

649
00:29:56,628 --> 00:29:57,796
come up this way?

650
00:29:59,230 --> 00:29:59,798
We were the same

651
00:29:59,831 --> 00:30:00,798
back then.

652
00:30:01,866 --> 00:30:02,433
Becoming a department director

653
00:30:02,433 --> 00:30:03,401
really does change a person.

654
00:30:05,370 --> 00:30:06,838
You don't sound human anymore.

655
00:30:12,877 --> 00:30:13,411
Zhou Xiaofeng.

656
00:30:17,849 --> 00:30:18,550
Is the Heart Center director position

657
00:30:18,583 --> 00:30:19,684
really that important?

658
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:21,319
Working overtime,

659
00:30:22,053 --> 00:30:22,921
competing over performance—

660
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:24,756
is that how you win?

661
00:30:26,691 --> 00:30:28,092
Have you really failed to see it?

662
00:30:28,626 --> 00:30:29,727
Have you never wondered

663
00:30:30,228 --> 00:30:31,529
why Cardiac Surgery's performance

664
00:30:31,529 --> 00:30:32,263
seems to have

665
00:30:32,263 --> 00:30:33,164
no ceiling?

666
00:30:33,765 --> 00:30:34,966
Why Director Sheng's numbers

667
00:30:35,033 --> 00:30:36,267
are so much higher

668
00:30:36,334 --> 00:30:37,068
than Director Jiang's used to be?

669
00:30:37,268 --> 00:30:37,769
It's simple.

670
00:30:37,802 --> 00:30:38,903
Director Sheng is more capable.

671
00:30:42,207 --> 00:30:43,308
If you want to take Director Sheng's side,

672
00:30:43,908 --> 00:30:44,509
go ahead.

673
00:30:45,476 --> 00:30:46,311
But let me tell you:

674
00:30:46,644 --> 00:30:47,345
I cannot lose.

675
00:30:49,214 --> 00:30:50,515
I don't have to become Heart Center director,

676
00:30:50,848 --> 00:30:51,683
but Sheng Nian absolutely cannot.

677
00:30:52,584 --> 00:30:54,118
I can't let him take that position.

678
00:30:55,286 --> 00:30:55,954
He doesn't deserve it.

679
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:13,438
Take her temperature every four hours.

680
00:31:17,475 --> 00:31:18,209
You're awake.

681
00:31:24,682 --> 00:31:25,350
You're awake.

682
00:31:27,986 --> 00:31:29,387
Tell me your name.

683
00:31:31,389 --> 00:31:32,757
Yiyi.

684
00:31:33,358 --> 00:31:34,292
How old are you?

685
00:31:36,828 --> 00:31:37,929
Twenty-four.

686
00:31:38,529 --> 00:31:39,197
Do you know

687
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:40,064
where you are now?

688
00:31:42,267 --> 00:31:43,568
The hospital.

689
00:31:47,472 --> 00:31:48,640
How do you feel?

690
00:31:51,509 --> 00:31:52,911
My chest hurts.

691
00:31:53,678 --> 00:31:54,612
Chest pain right now

692
00:31:54,646 --> 00:31:56,214
is normal after surgery.

693
00:31:56,514 --> 00:31:57,515
The operation was successful.

694
00:31:59,083 --> 00:32:00,451
If the pain gets severe,

695
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:01,552
call us.

696
00:32:02,287 --> 00:32:03,388
Thank you, doctor.

697
00:32:03,855 --> 00:32:04,889
Visiting starts this afternoon.

698
00:32:04,956 --> 00:32:05,823
Your family

699
00:32:05,890 --> 00:32:06,691
can come see you then.

700
00:32:10,962 --> 00:32:12,263
Everything is stable for now.

701
00:32:14,065 --> 00:32:14,599
My brother.

702
00:32:16,934 --> 00:32:18,102
I want to see my brother.

703
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:23,374
Uncle, Auntie.

704
00:32:23,708 --> 00:32:24,642
I'm sorry I'm late.

705
00:32:24,809 --> 00:32:25,443
I... I took

706
00:32:25,476 --> 00:32:26,444
the earliest flight here,

707
00:32:26,477 --> 00:32:27,111
but I still didn't make it.

708
00:32:27,679 --> 00:32:29,314
How is she now?

709
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:31,015
How did a nail gun

710
00:32:31,015 --> 00:32:32,050
fire into her heart?

711
00:32:35,687 --> 00:32:36,354
I'm sorry.

712
00:32:44,128 --> 00:32:44,529
Brother.

713
00:32:45,997 --> 00:32:46,531
It was me.

714
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:49,434
I accidentally fired the nail gun.

715
00:32:53,905 --> 00:32:54,572
I'm sorry.

716
00:33:08,786 --> 00:33:10,121
Family of Yan Yiyi.

717
00:33:10,388 --> 00:33:10,888
That's us.

718
00:33:12,357 --> 00:33:13,157
She's awake.

719
00:33:13,224 --> 00:33:14,192
Her condition is stable.

720
00:33:14,225 --> 00:33:14,959
The tube has been removed.

721
00:33:15,493 --> 00:33:16,794
You can visit at three o'clock.

722
00:33:17,161 --> 00:33:17,628
That's wonderful.

723
00:33:17,895 --> 00:33:18,329
That's wonderful.

724
00:33:18,596 --> 00:33:19,197
Thank you, doctor.

725
00:33:19,831 --> 00:33:20,798
You're her brother, right?

726
00:33:21,199 --> 00:33:22,066
The first thing she said after waking

727
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:23,000
was that she wanted to see you.

728
00:33:23,868 --> 00:33:24,969
Also, bring one or two

729
00:33:24,969 --> 00:33:25,703
photos of her

730
00:33:26,170 --> 00:33:27,005
that can encourage her.

731
00:33:27,472 --> 00:33:27,805
Okay.

732
00:33:27,839 --> 00:33:28,606
We have some.

733
00:33:29,107 --> 00:33:29,640
Phone.

734
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:55,133
Why are you cooking

735
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:56,067
in the hospital?

736
00:33:56,567 --> 00:33:57,735
No. Pack it up right now.

737
00:33:57,935 --> 00:33:59,170
It's almost done. Five minutes.

738
00:33:59,270 --> 00:34:00,071
What do you mean, five minutes?

739
00:34:00,071 --> 00:34:01,038
Not even one minute.

740
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:02,440
Private appliances are forbidden in the hallway.

741
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:03,708
It'll be ready soon. Just five minutes.

742
00:34:03,975 --> 00:34:04,709
No five minutes. Unplug it.

743
00:34:04,976 --> 00:34:05,710
What do you mean, five minutes?

744
00:34:05,843 --> 00:34:06,644
It'll be done very soon.

745
00:34:06,644 --> 00:34:06,878
You...

746
00:34:07,311 --> 00:34:07,678
Hurry.

747
00:34:08,112 --> 00:34:08,546
I'm telling you,

748
00:34:08,613 --> 00:34:09,747
if you keep this up, I'll call security.

749
00:34:09,847 --> 00:34:10,281
What's going on?

750
00:34:10,348 --> 00:34:10,948
Don't call security.

751
00:34:11,149 --> 00:34:11,816
Don't touch it.

752
00:34:12,483 --> 00:34:13,751
No one is allowed to touch it.

753
00:34:14,886 --> 00:34:16,487
Which bed are you in? Why won't you listen?

754
00:34:17,121 --> 00:34:17,889
Sister Yalan.

755
00:34:21,759 --> 00:34:22,727
I'm calling security right now.

756
00:34:23,528 --> 00:34:24,328
I know him.

757
00:34:25,363 --> 00:34:25,963
I'll talk to him.

758
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:27,732
You know him?

759
00:34:29,167 --> 00:34:29,467
Well...

760
00:34:30,868 --> 00:34:32,070
Then make him unplug it now.

761
00:34:32,637 --> 00:34:33,438
Okay. Don't worry.

762
00:34:39,710 --> 00:34:40,611
The hospital has rules.

763
00:34:40,745 --> 00:34:41,846
Small appliances aren't allowed.

764
00:34:42,947 --> 00:34:44,081
And there's a cafeteria downstairs.

765
00:34:44,115 --> 00:34:44,916
You can buy food there.

766
00:34:46,050 --> 00:34:48,052
No. They don't have it.

767
00:34:48,453 --> 00:34:49,153
Don't have what?

768
00:34:49,554 --> 00:34:49,954
Congee.

769
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:51,889
They have congee.

770
00:34:52,490 --> 00:34:53,157
No.

771
00:34:53,891 --> 00:34:54,992
No shredded wood ear.

772
00:34:55,326 --> 00:34:56,227
No shredded wood ear.

773
00:34:56,494 --> 00:34:57,995
West Lake beef soup without wood ear.

774
00:35:00,364 --> 00:35:02,033
The version with wood ear

775
00:35:02,033 --> 00:35:03,000
is delicious too.

776
00:35:03,267 --> 00:35:04,502
The cafeteria sells it.

777
00:35:07,205 --> 00:35:08,606
My sister likes it without wood ear.

778
00:35:10,975 --> 00:35:12,210
But you still can't cook here.

779
00:35:15,213 --> 00:35:16,314
It's close to the ICU.

780
00:35:17,315 --> 00:35:18,449
I wanted her to have something hot.

781
00:35:28,759 --> 00:35:29,527
Is it almost done?

782
00:35:31,395 --> 00:35:32,196
Then hurry.

783
00:35:32,530 --> 00:35:33,431
I'll keep watch for you.

784
00:35:48,746 --> 00:35:50,214
Have you been inside that ICU?

785
00:35:55,153 --> 00:35:56,787
What is it like in there?

786
00:35:57,788 --> 00:35:58,923
Do the people inside

787
00:36:00,758 --> 00:36:01,926
sleep at night?

788
00:36:02,527 --> 00:36:04,729
It's just rows of hospital beds.

789
00:36:06,197 --> 00:36:07,765
Everyone rests at night.

790
00:36:22,914 --> 00:36:23,948
What's your name?

791
00:36:25,182 --> 00:36:25,983
My name is Qiangwei.

792
00:36:30,555 --> 00:36:31,055
Thank you.

793
00:36:34,392 --> 00:36:34,926
What about you?

794
00:36:36,527 --> 00:36:37,195
What's your name?

795
00:36:38,429 --> 00:36:38,996
Yan Chunjing.

796
00:36:41,832 --> 00:36:42,633
Be careful.

797
00:36:52,677 --> 00:36:54,312
Help!

798
00:36:54,812 --> 00:36:57,248
Someone help!

799
00:37:08,893 --> 00:37:10,194
Go see Yiyi.

800
00:37:10,962 --> 00:37:12,163
Since she wants to see you,

801
00:37:12,330 --> 00:37:13,731
she must have something to say.

802
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:22,039
You should go.

803
00:37:30,514 --> 00:37:31,015
Uncle.

804
00:37:31,649 --> 00:37:32,049
Auntie.

805
00:37:32,650 --> 00:37:33,284
Could you

806
00:37:34,185 --> 00:37:35,353
let me go in and see Yiyi?

807
00:37:39,957 --> 00:37:41,726
Weren't you supposed to come back the day after tomorrow?

808
00:37:46,998 --> 00:37:47,665
Does it still hurt?

809
00:37:49,066 --> 00:37:50,134
What do you think?

810
00:37:54,572 --> 00:37:55,473
It doesn't.

811
00:37:56,674 --> 00:37:58,109
The surgery was under general anesthesia.

812
00:37:58,843 --> 00:37:59,644
I closed my eyes,

813
00:38:00,077 --> 00:38:00,811
then opened them,

814
00:38:01,512 --> 00:38:02,280
and I was here.

815
00:38:07,585 --> 00:38:08,986
How did your order go?

816
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:12,523
Pretty well.

817
00:38:15,593 --> 00:38:16,027
By the way,

818
00:38:16,994 --> 00:38:17,795
where's my brother?

819
00:38:19,797 --> 00:38:20,831
Did you see him?

820
00:38:22,066 --> 00:38:23,000
He's right outside.

821
00:38:29,874 --> 00:38:30,808
He made this for you.

822
00:38:31,409 --> 00:38:31,876
What do you think?

823
00:38:35,112 --> 00:38:36,414
No shredded wood ear.

824
00:38:40,584 --> 00:38:42,253
You two idiots.

825
00:38:43,354 --> 00:38:45,089
How am I supposed to eat this now?

826
00:38:50,528 --> 00:38:50,995
Look.

827
00:38:51,562 --> 00:38:52,329
See what I brought you.

828
00:38:56,233 --> 00:38:56,801
It hurts.

829
00:38:58,803 --> 00:38:59,236
It's okay.

830
00:39:00,071 --> 00:39:00,571
I'll do it.

831
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:23,794
What if someday

832
00:39:25,162 --> 00:39:26,664
I can't even apply lip balm

833
00:39:26,764 --> 00:39:28,165
by myself?

834
00:39:32,670 --> 00:39:33,504
I'll apply it for you.

835
00:39:36,574 --> 00:39:37,641
What about washing my hair?

836
00:39:38,442 --> 00:39:38,909
I'll wash it.

837
00:39:40,411 --> 00:39:41,078
Drying it?

838
00:39:42,546 --> 00:39:43,114
I'll dry it.

839
00:39:44,115 --> 00:39:44,915
Putting on my shoes?

840
00:39:46,083 --> 00:39:46,550
I'll put them on.

841
00:39:49,553 --> 00:39:50,054
Really?

842
00:39:51,756 --> 00:39:52,823
You'll always be here?

843
00:39:54,592 --> 00:39:55,092
Really.

844
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:57,128
I'll always be here.

845
00:40:07,104 --> 00:40:07,805
Sir, please make way.

846
00:40:09,273 --> 00:40:09,907
Slowly. Slowly.

847
00:40:10,107 --> 00:40:11,008
Director Sheng gave strict instructions.

848
00:40:11,409 --> 00:40:12,076
Don't damage it.

849
00:40:21,185 --> 00:40:22,153
Hello, Director Sheng.

850
00:40:23,254 --> 00:40:23,954
Okay. Right away.

851
00:40:24,188 --> 00:40:25,556
Mingde Hall. Yes, I remember.

852
00:40:27,091 --> 00:40:27,591
No problem.

853
00:40:27,625 --> 00:40:28,425
I won't crease it.

854
00:41:11,836 --> 00:41:12,870
This way, please.

855
00:41:13,170 --> 00:41:13,804
Do I sign here?

856
00:41:13,804 --> 00:41:15,206
Yes. Please sign here.

857
00:41:19,476 --> 00:41:19,877
Director Zhou.

858
00:41:20,110 --> 00:41:20,644
Long time no see.

859
00:41:22,713 --> 00:41:24,014
Last time, you went to Chengdu

860
00:41:24,081 --> 00:41:25,082
for the symposium.

861
00:41:25,115 --> 00:41:25,349
Yes.

862
00:41:25,516 --> 00:41:26,083
Today is clearly

863
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:27,251
Director Sheng's home turf.

864
00:41:27,518 --> 00:41:28,319
It really is different.

865
00:41:28,652 --> 00:41:29,253
Manager Ouyang.

866
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:31,789
Hello.

867
00:41:34,692 --> 00:41:36,193
We'll need your continued support.

868
00:41:36,827 --> 00:41:37,394
The symposium?

869
00:41:37,561 --> 00:41:37,928
Yes.

870
00:41:39,730 --> 00:41:40,231
Secretary-General Jiang.

871
00:41:40,464 --> 00:41:40,998
You're here.

872
00:41:41,932 --> 00:41:42,366
Hello.

873
00:41:42,399 --> 00:41:42,733
Hello.

874
00:41:43,801 --> 00:41:44,802
Secretary-General Jiang is here.

875
00:41:47,838 --> 00:41:48,205
Hello.

876
00:41:48,606 --> 00:41:49,173
Professor Jiang.

877
00:41:51,375 --> 00:41:52,142
Let's meet another time.

878
00:41:52,243 --> 00:41:52,810
Secretary-General Jiang.

879
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:53,944
What brings you here?

880
00:41:54,945 --> 00:41:56,313
Cardiovascular medicine isn't my field.

881
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:58,015
But lately I've been researching

882
00:41:58,249 --> 00:41:59,917
integrated heart-brain care,

883
00:42:00,084 --> 00:42:01,452
so I came to learn.

884
00:42:01,652 --> 00:42:02,653
It's an honor

885
00:42:02,753 --> 00:42:03,687
to have you here guiding us.

886
00:42:05,856 --> 00:42:06,290
Ouyang.

887
00:42:07,424 --> 00:42:08,559
Professor, why are you here?

888
00:42:09,393 --> 00:42:10,594
Of course I'm here for the conference.

889
00:42:10,928 --> 00:42:11,362
Otherwise,

890
00:42:11,829 --> 00:42:13,030
did you think I came to surprise you?

891
00:42:13,430 --> 00:42:15,165
Manager Ouyang was your student, right?

892
00:42:16,667 --> 00:42:18,335
This disappointing student of mine

893
00:42:19,370 --> 00:42:20,838
changed careers halfway through.

894
00:42:21,605 --> 00:42:23,040
I hope she hasn't caused you trouble.

895
00:42:23,240 --> 00:42:23,807
Not at all.

896
00:42:24,174 --> 00:42:24,842
Manager Ouyang

897
00:42:25,042 --> 00:42:26,210
is smart and capable,

898
00:42:26,543 --> 00:42:28,045
and especially dependable.

899
00:42:28,145 --> 00:42:28,712
She has provided us

900
00:42:28,746 --> 00:42:29,513
with a great deal of help.

901
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:31,248
A great teacher produces a fine student.

902
00:42:32,850 --> 00:42:33,384
Truly.

903
00:42:34,184 --> 00:42:35,319
I wouldn't dare embarrass my professor.

904
00:42:35,686 --> 00:42:36,120
Secretary-General,

905
00:42:36,587 --> 00:42:36,954
please have a seat.

906
00:42:40,925 --> 00:42:41,959
Back in school,

907
00:42:41,992 --> 00:42:43,227
I spoiled her too much.

908
00:42:43,427 --> 00:42:45,029
At gatherings with our academic peers,

909
00:42:45,162 --> 00:42:46,664
she never knew when to help out.

910
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:48,265
But look at her now.

911
00:42:49,633 --> 00:42:50,634
She's even learned

912
00:42:50,668 --> 00:42:52,036
to serve tea and water.

913
00:42:53,637 --> 00:42:55,039
Looks like

914
00:42:55,506 --> 00:42:57,041
Dongli Hospital really builds character.
